@NODE Overview


PICAsm is an Amiga cross assembler for 12, 14 and 16 bit microcontroller from
microchip. PICAsm uses the microchip commands and many features of microchip`s
mpasm assembler. 

The generated INHX8 file includes this: Program Memory (if used)
					EEPROM memory  (if used)
					Device settings ( OSC, CP, etc ).




Questions, criticism, suggestions and @{"bug reports" LINK BugReports} are always welcome.






@ENDNODE




@NODE processors



12 bit types:

- PIC16C54
- PIC16C55
- PIC16C56
- PIC16C57
- PIC16C58


14 bit types:

- PIC16C61
- PIC16C62
- PIC16C64
- PIC16C65
- PIC16C620
- PIC16C621
- PIC16C622
- PIC16C71
- PIC16C73
- PIC16C74
- PIC16C84


16 bit types:

- PIC17C42
- PIC17C43
- PIC17C44
		





@ENDNODE







